Currently, when you attach files to a page via the viewpageattachments.action page, you can only add a comment, and the name in confluence defaults to the file name. I know you can go to the properties and change the name of the file after uploading it, but this is cumbersome when there are lots of files that need to be uploaded and organized. Please add a file name input field to the attachments page so you can set the file name as you upload the attachment.

I have a multicolumn table. I want the 1st column to be right-justified and the 2nd column to be left-justified. I can't do this so I have to adjust each cell individually. I also want some of the text in the 2nd column to be indented, so I added spaces in front of the items. If I click right justify on a cell in the 1st column, it removes leading spaces for items in the 2nd column.

